<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,930,1116]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,282,930,956]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[291,433,931,956]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Apoxyptilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[291,433,931,956]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">Apoxyptilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the absence of a pronounced ventral scale brush on the second segment of the labial palpus; a strongly oblique termen of the second lobe of the forewing; the distance between the subapical and apical scale teeth exceeding three times the length of the subapical tooth; male genitalia with the uncus reduced and the valva without a valvular lobe; and female genitalia with a cylindrical antrum and lacking a signum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
